pc|DQ|pc|D8|pc|S2|pc|H3|at|(which had been dealt to Geir) as Eddie discarded a heart on this trick. |
pg| ***** 39 ***** |


nt|The contract was safe as there was no way that I could lose more than 1 trick in each suit. The Cavendish Pairs is scored using IMPs so overtricks are not critically important, but they are definitely not to be sneezed at (especially given the strength of the field in this event). Do you see any chance of making an overtrick in 3@D?|
pg| ***** 40 ***** |


hs|nh|hs|sh|nt|In fact, there is almost no legitimate technical chance to make an overtrick on this deal, especially against such strong defenders. I considered ducking a heart trick in an attempt to improve my squeeze chances. |
pg| ***** 41 ***** |


ls|sd|ls|nh|ls|sh|hs|sd|at|I also considered running all of my trumps immediately. I just didn't think that either of these plays would work. |
pg| ***** 42 ***** |


ls|sd|nt|I was able to think of a non-technical chance (that is, a swindle) that I thought was much more likely to work than any legitimate play. Can you think of what I did? |
pg| ***** 43 ***** |


ls|sd|hs|nc|hs|sc|sk||hs|wc|at|I tried the effect of a low club toward dummy's @C10, hoping that Geir had been dealt the @CJ and that it would not be clear to him to win the trick with that card! |
pg| ***** 44 ***** |


nt||ls|sc|ls|wc|ls|nc|
pc|C4|hs|wc|at|Geir gave my @C4 some serious thought, but he eventually made the very reasonable play of ducking his @CJ! |
pg| ***** 45 ***** |


ls|wc|pc|C3|
at|If you think I am writing about this deal in order to show off for having tricked the great Helgemo, you have it all wrong. In fact, I probably would not have tried this swindle against most players, but Geir was certainly good enough to duck his @CJ if it looked like the right play. |
pg| ***** 46 ***** |


hs|nc|nt|So it was my profound respect for my left hand opponent that made me adopt this unusual line of play, but the same factor made it all the more satisfying when the @C10 won the trick! |
pg| ***** 47 ***** |


ls|nc|pc|CT|pc|C2|
pg| ***** 48 ***** |


hs|ns|hs|ss|hs|es|at|I tried to sneak a spade through next, but Eddie (who had a much easier problem then Geir had on the trick before) went up with his @SA. |
pg| ***** 49 ***** |


